modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and manipulating MLd (Markdown-like) syntax, including converting headers, lists, and code blocks to structured data. Operates on strings and custom AST nodes representing document elements. Used to generate HTML output from annotated source files and validate formatting rules during documentation builds.

Handles path manipulation and tag-based filtering for build processes. Operates on pathname and string types, enabling tasks like directory traversal, file tagging, and rule creation. Used to generate build rules, filter files by tags, and manage visibility of generated files.
